

ðŸ§¿Array
- An array in java is a container  object that holds a fixed number of value of a single data type 

- its use to store multiple records 
- elements acces using index
- index start from 0

1) declaration 
--> int[] number;
    int number[];

2) creation of array
--> number=new int[4];
    number[]=new int[4];

3) initialization 
--> int a[]={1,3,5,7,8,5};

4) Accessing array elements 
 --> System.out.println(a[0]);
 -->output 1

5) memory Allocation for single value 

 --> ob[0]=new Emp();  

6) memory Allocation for single value 

--> for(i=0;i<n;i++)
     {
       ob[i]=new Emp();
     }

------------------------------------

ðŸ‘‰ Accept n record 

for(i=0;i<n;i++)
 {
  ob[i]=new Emp();
  ob[i].disp();
 }

ðŸ‘‰ display n record 
 
 for(i=0;i<n;i++)
 {
  ob[i].disp();
 }

